<TITLE> 8 killed in two road crashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 27 (bdnews24.com)  At least eight persons were killed and 12 others injured in two road crashes in Tangail and Faridpur early on Thursday. Five people died and 10 others were injured when a Jaipurhat bound bus of Hanif Paribahan crashed into a truck on the Dhaka-Tangail highway at Ashekpur at around 4am, said Salauddin, sergeant of the highway police. The truck fell into a roadside ditch, he said. Among the dead, three have been as identified as Ranju, 25 and Manjur Ahmed, 24, of Jaipurhat and Babul Akhter, 45, of Naogaon. The injured were admitted to Tangail general hospital. The bus driver managed to flee, the police officer said. In Faridpur, three people were killed when a Dhaka bound bus coming from Barguna turned upside down on the Dhaka-Barisal highway at Maligram area at around 1am, Bhanga police chief Abdur Razzak said. The dead have been identified as Nasima Akhter, 35, her daughter Pushpita, 7, of Kishoreganj and Masud Miah, 38 of Barguna. Two other passengers injured in the accident - identified as Shahabuddin and Selim Miah of Barguna - were admitted to Faridpur Medical College Hospital. bd
